english:
  title: Blue Prayer to the Big Dipper
  author: Lee Gyu-bo
  language: eng
  text: The heavens are clear and dwell on high, stirring one vital breath through the source of the Way. The Big Dipper turns at the center, governing all life in the realm below. Its watchfulness extends not far; trust may be placed in its presence. Yet turning my thoughts inward, this frail and humble form has undeservedly taken on the heavy burden of guiding a nation through trials—how the spirit labors! Though I lack exceptional gifts, Heaven's mandate is not easily fulfilled; thus I tremble before such luminous scrutiny. And now that those pure celestial chariots descend to pause precisely at this moment, I must pour forth my burning devotion and raise my eyes to beseech great blessings. I examine the lesser rites within the register of immortals and solemnly perform the sacred ceremonies upon the spiritual altar. May the High and True look down upon this simple, humble offering with favor, grant years of enduring life to be inscribed in the Jade Record for eternal being, and extend boundless grace to preserve and protect this realm in perpetuity.
  footnotes:
    - The Big Dipper (北斗) held profound significance in East Asian cosmology and governance, symbolizing divine order and the connection between heaven and earthly rule.
    - This appears to be a prayer or invocation composed by an official seeking celestial blessing for the stability and prosperity of the realm.
    - The 'Jade Record' (玉籍) references the heavenly book where the fates and lifespans of mortals are inscribed.
